alert.note: Alert for San Juan County; Western Skagit County; Western Whatcom County (Washington) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 28 at 2:56AM PST until January 29 at 6:00AM PST by NWS Seattle
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM THIS EVENING TO 6 AM PST SUNDAY... * WHAT...Northeast winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts up to 50 mph expected. * WHERE...San Juan County, Western Whatcom County and Western Skagit County. * WHEN...From 6 PM today to 6 AM PST Sunday. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Temperatures will drop overnight with wind chill values in the single digits by early Sunday morning, away from the water in Whatcom County.
info.instruction: Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
